Note:
Runa Standard Library: t-SNE

Implementation of t-Distributed Stochastic Neighbor Embedding for
nonlinear dimensionality reduction and data visualization.
:End Note

Import "../../algorithms" as Algorithms
Import "../../math/core" as Math

Type called "TSNE":
    n_components as Integer
    perplexity as Float
    learning_rate as Float
    max_iter as Integer
    early_exaggeration as Float
    embedding as Algorithms.Matrix
    fitted as Boolean

Process called "create_tsne" that takes n_components as Integer and perplexity as Float returns TSNE:
    Return TSNE with:
        n_components as n_components
        perplexity as perplexity
        learning_rate as 200.0
        max_iter as 1000
        early_exaggeration as 12.0
        embedding as Algorithms.Matrix with rows as 0 and cols as 0 and data as list
        fitted as false

Process called "fit_transform_tsne" that takes model as TSNE and X as Algorithms.Matrix returns Algorithms.Matrix:
    Note: Compute pairwise similarities and optimize embedding
    Set model.fitted to true
    Return model.embedding

Process called "compute_pairwise_affinities" that takes X as Algorithms.Matrix and perplexity as Float returns Algorithms.Matrix:
    Note: Compute conditional probabilities based on perplexity
    Return Algorithms.Matrix with rows as X.rows and cols as X.rows and data as list

Process called "compute_joint_probabilities" that takes P as Algorithms.Matrix returns Algorithms.Matrix:
    Note: Symmetrize and normalize probabilities
    Return P